ou may incur long distance charges from your cell phone service provider if you dial an access number that is not local. Your usual air time and local charges from your service provider still apply.\r\n<h4>Do I have to press the SEND KEY again after I dial the long distance number I wish to call?</h4>\r\nNo, you don’t have to. After dialing the G3 Access Number, press the SEND key only once. When you hear the voice prompt, dial the long distance number you wish to call. DO NOT PRESS THE SEND KEY AGAIN.\r\n<h4>Do your rates differ when using a landline versus a cell phone for long distance?</h4>\r\nNo, with InTouch America Power by G3 Telecom you can enjoy the SAME LOW long distance rates when using your cell phone or home phone, 24 hours a day, 7 days a week!\r\n\r\n<em>*When using your cell phone, you will still be charged your usual air time and any applicable roaming charges by your cell phone service provider.</em>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://www.intouchamerica.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/welcome-letter.pdf\">Click Here</a> to review some useful tips and information that is provided for your convenience', 'FAQ', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '133-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-06-07 04:47:43', '2017-06-07 04:47:43', '', 133, 'http://anvinfosystem.com/intouch_america/2017/06/07/133-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
